Activity, LinkListener
public class Wait
extends AbstractBasicActivity

The wait activity specifies a delay for a certain period of time or until a certain deadline is reached (see section 8.3. Expressions for the grammar of duration expressions and deadline expressions). If the specified duration value in for is zero or negative, or a specified deadline in until has already been reached or passed, then the wait activity completes immediately. [10.7]

Tim Hallwyl
